<subSubSection id="AEAE65763A4DFFAF63B8FCBFFA9EFC54" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E60B36FD3A4DFFAF63B8FCBFFA9EFC54" blockId="1.[151,1436,810,948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="D4C0EAEF3A4DFFAF63B8FCBFFC81FCA4" bold="true" box="[151,855,810,836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Diagnosis (comparative to other 
<taxonomicName id="21B44D7E3A4DFFAF616DFCBFFD3BFCA4" box="[578,749,810,836]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Augochlorini">Augochlorini</taxonomicName>
genera)
</emphasis>
. Prementum greatly elongate, more than seven times longer than wide; ocelli greatly enlarged, distance between lateral ocellus and compound eye less than one ocellus diameter; pronotal lobes not angled or carinate; basal area of metapostnotum not striate; inner hind tibial spur pectinate, but with short branches; outer surface of metatibia with patch of black setae.
</paragraph>
